Where we stand and learn to slow down

00:25:08.720 --> 00:25:13.260
The line clears, but
the light remains

00:25:13.880 --> 00:25:22.960
A soft room, a soft lane

00:25:40.760 --> 00:25:46.400
Cart at the corner, lamp on low

00:25:47.360 --> 00:25:52.120
One warm circle on the floor

00:25:52.880 --> 00:25:56.180
The cart is packed and nearly still

00:25:56.780 --> 00:26:01.580
You slide the lamp
toward the window sill

00:26:02.180 --> 00:26:07.680
A little pool of gold on the aisle

00:26:08.120 --> 00:26:14.740
A small, certain way to tie the night

00:26:14.980 --> 00:26:17.720
No big finish, no bright chase

00:26:17.780 --> 00:26:20.680
Just a steady shape, a little grace

00:26:20.740 --> 00:26:23.400
I don't need a phrase
that proves it all

00:26:23.460 --> 00:26:26.620
I just keep the light
when voices call

00:26:26.920 --> 00:26:31.500
Cart-side table lamp, late and low

00:26:32.000 --> 00:26:35.780
Keeps the room from going cold

00:26:36.580 --> 00:26:41.960
We stay with the same calm line

00:26:42.460 --> 00:27:13.920
And I feel this
moment still feel fine

00:27:13.980 --> 00:27:18.740
You hold one edge of the
tote, then set it down

00:27:19.420 --> 00:27:24.360
The lamp hums soft above the town

00:27:25.260 --> 00:27:29.600
Outside the street goes soft and thin

00:27:30.860 --> 00:27:35.020
Inside, the song slows
and lets us begin

00:27:35.980 --> 00:27:40.160
If this was just a long afternoon

00:27:40.260 --> 00:27:43.040
Then this calm note is the proof

00:27:43.100 --> 00:27:46.860
That a shared pause
can hold two minds

00:27:46.920 --> 00:27:53.280
Without a speech or a binding sign

00:27:53.340 --> 00:27:58.160
Cart-side table lamp, late and low

00:27:58.580 --> 00:28:02.400
Keeps the room from going cold

00:28:03.780 --> 00:28:08.520
A warm glow stays through the aisle

00:28:08.840 --> 00:28:17.200
Long after the line
in the day goes mild

00:28:46.120 --> 00:28:51.160
Last store light on the table

00:28:51.700 --> 00:28:57.180
Door at the edge, still able

00:28:58.320 --> 00:29:01.340
The close bell hums once, then twice

00:29:01.420 --> 00:29:04.400
A slow light turns
warm and quiet twice

00:29:04.480 --> 00:29:07.500
You set your bag near
the edge of the tray

00:29:07.580 --> 00:29:10.400
I nod, and the room
starts to fade away

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:13.540
No final answer, no final line

00:29:13.620 --> 00:29:16.680
Only this soft little night in time

00:29:16.760 --> 00:29:19.920
A place we shared, then set down

00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:22.860
A gentle close, not upside-down

00:29:22.940 --> 00:29:26.260
Last bookstore hour, soft and clear

00:29:26.340 --> 00:29:29.240
Keeps the hope a little near

00:29:29.320 --> 00:29:32.580
Not a finish, only a turn

00:29:32.680 --> 00:29:35.640
We keep this little light to burn

00:29:36.300 --> 00:29:39.120
Shadows climb, then touch the floor

00:29:39.200 --> 00:29:42.000
Your hand points down
the darkened door

00:29:42.080 --> 00:29:44.360
We leave the bookish air behind

00:29:45.080 --> 00:29:48.820
But not the calm it taught us to find

00:29:49.060 --> 00:29:52.480
If this stays open a little more

00:29:52.560 --> 00:29:55.160
We'll meet the day at the back door

00:29:55.240 --> 00:29:58.900
If this stays closed
for now it's fine

00:29:59.440 --> 00:30:18.030
The good part stays,
and the song stays mine

00:30:18.110 --> 00:30:22.030
Last bookstore hour, soft and clear

00:30:22.110 --> 00:30:25.150
Keeps the hope a little near

00:30:27.210 --> 00:30:30.430
Paper breath, lamp light, slow track

00:30:30.510 --> 00:30:34.630
The hour lets go, then comes back
